  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enabling Better Institutional and Operational Response Capacity to Climate Change and Disasters in Mauritania</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project&#x2019;s overall objective is to improve the institutional and operational capacity of the Mauritanian government as well as NGOs in disaster risk reduction, preparedness and response by developing an up-to-date national contingency plan that will enhance the country&#x2019;s preparedness to major disasters. This plan includes a resource inventory and contingency stocks system, formulated from an accurate risk and needs assessment, and engages vulnerable communities and local authorities with the objective of making them more resilient and able to properly manage climate change-induced internal displacement. The project focuses on 3 main components: updating the national contingency plan to include a broad range of disasters and formulating a national resource inventory and contingency stocks plan; strengthening and equipping the contingency stock systems and mechanisms to manage and prepare disaster risks reduction; and engaging local communities to ensure they are able to respond to disaster in a way that looks at the medium-long term impacts on their socio economic and development aspects.</narrative>
  </description>
